The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Cristiano to insist on transfer
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Cristiano to insist on transfer
            In amp; Out                
	 Cristiano Ronaldo will demand to be allowed to move to Real Madrid when he returns to Old Trafford on Tuesday after the Spanish champions publicly reiterated their desire to sign the Portuguese winger. After weeks of speculation, Ronaldo will attempt to force Manchester Uniteds hand by meeting Sir Alex Ferguson, the manager, and David Gill, the chief executive, to insist he be allowed to move to the Bernabeu. Bernd Schuster, the Madrid coach, confirmed that Real are continuing to work on a deal.         
	Barry move         
	 Liverpool have been given renewed hope of signing Gareth Barry from Aston Villa with Martin Neill, the Villa manager, conceding that the player could move to Anfield after all. But Arsenal will attempt to lure Barry to north London.         
	Tottenham bid         
	 Tottenham look set to fail with an 18m bid for West Ham striker Dean Ashton, who the Hammers insist is not for sale. To sign Zenit St Petersburg striker Andrei Arshavin, Tottenham must pay 19m as well as make him the highest-paid player in the world, while Midfielder Aaron Lennon is set to reject a move to Newcastle.         
	Scolari hope         
	 Chelsea manager Luiz Felipe Scolari expects midfielder Frank Lampard to sign a new contract with the Blues. Hes is also confident Didier Drogba will agree a new contract, which will see the striker pick up 100,000 a week.         
	Everton ploy         
	 Everton manager David Moyes will bid 3m for Manchester United midfielder Darren Fletcher. Fulham boss Roy Hodgson wants Everton striker Andy Johnson but for less than the 10.5m asking price.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                        
